  "body": "*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: User is logged out when leaving Status running at the background and sharing a picture via Gmail at the same time\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nAs a user I want to get back to the Status app running in the background\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nSession breaks, need to re-login\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n*PRECONDITION: open any screenshot in the gallery and leave it running in the background. Then:\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Enter password and login\r\n- Using the device button switch to the screenshot in the gallery\r\n- Click Share icon and select gmail app\r\n- Wait untill the attachment is added\r\n- Using the device button switch to the Status app\r\n\r\nhttps://drive.google.com/open?id=0B7h1U1joPifRc1RwS3RUQ1JySm8\r\n\r\n*Summary*: Session should not break when operating with other applications while Status is in the background\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n* Status version: 0.9.7+\r\n* Operating System: Android\r\n* Gmail version 7.1.29.147605088\r\n* [2017_05_23_16_30_22 - logcat.txt](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/1022339/2017_05_23_16_30_22.-.logcat.txt)\r\n",
